7.1.7 - M365SR07: Lack of Organisation Branding on Microsoft Login Portal
ISM controls:
•	Control: 1152; Revision: 4; Updated: Dec-22; Applicability: All; OS: All (Establishing a security awareness program)
•	Control: 0957; Revision: 7; Updated: Sep-23; Applicability: All; OS: All (Restricting access to systems and applications)
•	Control: 1560; Revision: 3; Updated: Dec-22; Applicability: All; OS: All (Configuration of cloud services)
________________________________________
Current Risk
Lack of organisation branding on the Microsoft Login portal decreases end-user awareness of phishing attacks which may result in the compromise of agency systems and information.
Risk Assessment:
Risk Likelihood	x	Risk Consequence	=	Risk Rating
ALMOST CERTAIN	x	MODERATE	=	HIGH
________________________________________
Recommendations:
1.	Customise Tenant Branding: Configure the Entra ID Company Branding settings with the official agency logo, background images, and a specific "Sign-in page text" footer to distinguish the legitimate portal from generic phishing sites.
2.	Enforce FIDO2/Passwordless Authentication: Transition users to phishing-resistant authentication methods (e.g., Windows Hello for Business or FIDO2 security keys) to mitigate the impact of a user entering credentials into a fraudulent site.
3.	Implement Integrated Phishing Simulations: Conduct regular training exercises that specifically educate users to look for the agency's custom branding as a validation step during the authentication flow.
- Treatment #1
•	Portal Configuration: Upload high-resolution agency-specific assets to the Entra ID Branding blade, ensuring the branding persists across all supported languages.
•	Help Desk Integration: Update the custom "Post-Sign-in" text to provide direct links to the agency's IT support portal and security reporting instructions.
•	Phishing Reporting Mechanism: Deploy the "Report Message" add-in in Outlook to allow users to quickly flag suspicious login requests that lack the expected custom branding.
________________________________________
Residual risk outcome if recommendation is implemented.
While branding alone is not a fail-safe security control, it serves as a vital visual cue for user verification. Combined with phishing-resistant MFA, the likelihood of a user successfully being phished via a generic landing page is significantly reduced. This shifts the likelihood from "Almost Certain" to "Unlikely."
Risk Likelihood	x	Risk Consequence	=	Risk Rating
UNLIKELY	x	MODERATE	=	MEDIUM

